00:30:38.664 --> 00:30:40.580
I was having a conversation
with a good friend

00:30:40.580 --> 00:30:41.320
of mine, a young lady.

00:30:41.320 --> 00:30:43.486
Her name's Cody [? Denouier. ?]
She lives back home.

00:30:43.486 --> 00:30:46.360
She's an incredible
singer, incredible artist.

00:30:46.360 --> 00:30:48.700
And we were talking about
home and just all the stuff

00:30:48.700 --> 00:30:50.950
our relatives are going
through, and we both concluded

00:30:50.950 --> 00:30:53.480
that there's things where
I'm from that will kill you,

00:30:53.480 --> 00:30:55.804
and there's things that
will save our lives.

00:30:55.804 --> 00:30:57.970
There's things that are
killing people I love there,

00:30:57.970 --> 00:30:59.870
but there's things
there that I can't

00:30:59.870 --> 00:31:01.860
get anywhere else in the world.

00:31:01.860 --> 00:31:04.030
And we wrestle with that.

00:31:04.030 --> 00:31:06.380
And so I think this song
is an example of that.

00:31:06.380 --> 00:31:08.300
It's called "Wild West".

00:31:08.300 --> 00:31:09.837
And this song is about my home.

00:31:09.837 --> 00:31:11.670
I come from place they
called the Wild West.

00:31:11.670 --> 00:31:13.410
Cowboys and Indians, they said.

00:31:13.410 --> 00:31:15.820
And it's still the Wild West.

00:31:15.820 --> 00:31:17.220
We're still fighting
that battle.

00:31:17.220 --> 00:31:19.240
It just has a different face.

00:31:19.240 --> 00:31:22.840
And the Wild West was always
told from the cowboy's

00:31:22.840 --> 00:31:25.120
perspective, so I guess
this is a perspective

00:31:25.120 --> 00:31:28.330
